<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key C, 4/4. Em-centered hymn with chromatic passing chords.
- F#° substituted as ② (D major) for diatonic purity. B° as vii°.
- A (secondary dominant) kept as ⑥ label.
- LH "33" triads, half-note harmonic rhythm throughout.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH bass steps E→F→G→C in bars 1-4; Am→G counter-motion to melody.
- RH descends at bar 14: E5→C5 while LH climbs.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Verse 1 builds; middle bridge (9-12) reaches peak; final verse quieter with Am resolution.
-->
